<p class=3D"mb-8 last:mb-0">Let's dive in!</p>
<h2 class=3D"h2 text-dark mb-8" style=3D"scroll-margin-top: 100px" id=3D"wh=
at-is-chromedp">What Is Chromedp?</h2>
<p class=3D"mb-8 last:mb-0"><a class=3D"underline hover:text-blue" target=
=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener noreferrer nofollow" href=3D"https://github.com=
/chromedp/chromedp" style=3D"outline: none;">Chromedp</a> is a Golang libra=
ry for controlling Chrome in headless mode through the <a class=3D"underlin=
e hover:text-blue" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener noreferrer nofollow" h=
ref=3D"https://chromedevtools.github.io/devtools-protocol/" style=3D"outlin=
e: none;">DevTools Protocol.</a> This browser automation tool is great to p=
erform testing, simulate user interaction, or scrape online. To learn more,=
 check out our article about <a class=3D"underline hover:text-blue" target=
=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener" href=3D"https://www.zenrows.com/blog/headless-=
browser-scraping" style=3D"outline: none;">headless browser scraping</a>.</=
p>
<p class=3D"mb-8 last:mb-0">Also, Chromedp enables scraping dynamic-content=
 sites where JavaScript execution is crucial. Learn more in our in-depth gu=
ide on <a class=3D"underline hover:text-blue" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noop=
ener" href=3D"https://www.zenrows.com/blog/web-scraping-golang" style=3D"ou=
tline: none;">web scraping in Golang</a>.</p>
<h2 class=3D"h2 text-dark mb-8" style=3D"scroll-margin-top: 100px" id=3D"ge=
tting-started">Getting Started</h2>
<p class=3D"mb-8 last:mb-0">Follow this step-by-step section to set up a Ch=
romedp Go environment.</p>
