x" id=3D"set-up-a-go-project">1. Set Up a Go Project</h3>
<p class=3D"mb-8 last:mb-0">Make sure you have Go on your computer. Otherwi=
se, <a class=3D"underline hover:text-blue" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopene=
r noreferrer nofollow" href=3D"https://go.dev/dl/" style=3D"outline: none;"=
>download the Golang installer</a>, execute it, and follow the installation=
 wizard.
After setting it up, it's time to initialize a Chromedp project. Create a <=
code>chromedp-project</code> folder and enter it in the terminal:</p>
