                        <p class=3D"mb-8 last:mb-0">Well done! You master t=
he fundamentals of Chromedp now!</p>
<p class=3D"mb-8 last:mb-0">The content only involved ten elements because =
the page relies on infinite scrolling, so let's see how to scrape all produ=
cts in the next section of this tutorial.</p>
<h2 class=3D"h2 text-dark mb-8" style=3D"scroll-margin-top: 100px" id=3D"in=
teract-with-web-pages">Interact with Web Pages: Chromedp Pagination, Screen=
shot, etc.</h2>
<p class=3D"mb-8 last:mb-0">Chromdp gives you access to all headless browse=
r interactions, including moving the mouse, scrolling, waiting for elements=
, and more. These actions help you bypass <a class=3D"underline hover:text-=
blue" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener" href=3D"https://www.zenrows.com/bl=
og/anti-bot" style=3D"outline: none;">anti-bot</a> <a class=3D"underline ho=
ver:text-blue" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener" href=3D"https://www.zenro=
ws.com/blog/anti-bot" style=3D"outline: none;"></a>measures <a class=3D"und=
erline hover:text-blue" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener" href=3D"https://=
www.zenrows.com/blog/anti-bot" style=3D"outline: none;"></a>as your automat=
ed script will behave like a human user.</p>
<p class=3D"mb-4">The interactions supported by Chromedp include:</p>
<ul class=3D"mb-4 mt-4 pl-4 list-inside list-disc">
<li>Scroll down or up the page.</li>
<li>Chromedp pagination to handle multi-page scraping by navigating through=
 dynamic pages.</li>
<li>Click page elements and perform other mouse actions.</li>
<li>Wait for page elements to load.</li>
<li>Fill out and clear input fields.</li>
<li>Submit forms.</li>
<li>Take screenshots.</li>
<li>Export the page to a PDF.</li>
<li>Drag and drop elements.</li>
</ul>
<p class=3D"mb-8 last:mb-0">You can achieve those operations through common=
 <code>Run</code> actions or via the <a class=3D"underline hover:text-blue"=
 target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener noreferrer nofollow" href=3D"https://pkg=
.go.dev/github.com/chromedp/chromedp#Evaluate" style=3D"outline: none;"><co=
de>Evaluate()</code></a> function. This special action accepts a JavaScript=
 snippet as input and executes it on the page. With both tools, any browser=
 interaction becomes possible.</p>
<p class=3D"mb-8 last:mb-0">Let's take a look at how <code>Evaluate()</code=
> helps you scrape all products from the <a class=3D"underline hover:text-b=
lue" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener noreferrer nofollow" href=3D"https:/=
/scrapingclub.com/exercise/list_infinite_scroll/" style=3D"outline: none;">=
infinite scroll demo page</a> and then explore other popular Chromedp inter=
actions!</p>
<h3 class=3D"h4 font-title text-dark mb-8" style=3D"scroll-margin-top: 100p=
x" id=3D"scrolling">Scrolling</h3>
<p class=3D"mb-8 last:mb-0">After the first page load of our target <a clas=
s=3D"underline hover:text-blue" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener noreferre=
r nofollow" href=3D"https://scrapingclub.com/exercise/list_infinite_scroll/=
" style=3D"outline: none;">demo shop</a>, the page only contains ten produc=
ts, as it relies on infinite scrolling to load new data. Dealing with that =
popular interaction requires some JavaScript logic. This is where Chromedp =
pagination comes in.</p>
<p class=3D"mb-8 last:mb-0">Javascript-based pagination is essential when s=
craping websites that use dynamic page loading triggered by scrolling or cl=
icking "Load More" buttons. The code below instructs the browser to scroll =
down the page eight times at an interval of 0.5 seconds via JS.</p>
           =20
       =20
           =20
       =20
                    <div class=3D"mt-4 code-block-with-header relative" dat=
a-id=3D"content-block__code-header-49">
                <div class=3D"bg-inactive text-gray text-base py-3 px-5 rou=
nded-t-lg">
                    script.js
                </div>
       =20
        <div class=3D"mb-8 text-sm " id=3D"_xJNC2sUMmB68VEhUXxV2" data-id=
=3D"content-block__code-49">
            <pre><code class=3D"language-javascript hljs javascript" data-l=
ang=3D"javascript">    <span class=3D"hljs-comment">// scroll down the page=
 8 times</span>
    <span class=3D"hljs-keyword">const</span> scrolls =3D <span class=3D"hl=
js-number">8</span>
    <span class=3D"hljs-keyword">let</span> scrollCount =3D <span class=3D"=
hljs-number">0</span>
   =20
    <span class=3D"hljs-comment">// scroll down and then wait for 0.5s</spa=
n>
    <span class=3D"hljs-keyword">const</span> scrollInterval =3D setInterva=
l(<span class=3D"hljs-function"><span class=3D"hljs-params">()</span> =3D&g=
